						               													<description>Movies have the power to excite and inspire, to elicit gasps and tears from audiences, to linger in memory for a lifetime. There is no question movies have moved multitudes. But for you, a powerful Hollywood executive, movies are just an elevator pitch and a high-stakes gamble. Let those directors and critics sweat the details when it comes to a film&amp;rsquo;s &amp;ldquo;artistic merit.&amp;rdquo; All you care about is&amp;hellip; the BIG PICTURE!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Big Picture is a card game for 2-4 creative players about funding and releasing big budget movies in the hopes of securing a financial hit. From your lofty perspective, movies only amount to a few ideas thrown together and backed up with a several million bucks so they can lure different demographics into the theaters. The real trick is in timing your movie&amp;rsquo;s release so it can go down in history as a box office smash rather than a humiliating flop.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Big Picture is a &amp;ldquo;Make-as-You-Play&amp;rdquo; game, which means that this game starts with a few materials: index cards, a print-out to track market trends, and a few coins. Players will modify cards during the game as they create the movies that will cement their place in the annals of Hollywood.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As movies are added to the deck, each future game will draw on the imagination of past games. The deck can grow indefinitely, preserving a legacy of movies and ideas. Players can return to the saga of their Hollywood executive careers over and over for gambles on brand new motion picture releases.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
